Section 409 of the Income-Tax Act, 2025 reads as follows:
"A person shall be deemed to be an assessee in default, if such person—
(a) does not pay on the date specified in section 408, any instalment of the advance tax that he is required to pay by an order of the Assessing Officer under section 407(1) and (4);
(b) does not send to the Assessing Officer an intimation under section 407(8) on or before the date on which any such instalment as is not paid becomes due;
(c) does not pay on the basis of his estimate of his current income, the advance tax payable by him under section 407(9), in respect of such instalment or instalments."

The requirements under Section 211 of the Income-Tax Act, 2025 (as amended by the Finance Act, 2026) are:
- The total income of an assessee including any income received or receivable by way of participating in games or sports in India;
- Any income received or receivable by way of advertising or contributing to games or sports in India;
- Any amount guaranteed to be paid or payable to a non-resident sports association or institution in relation to any game or sport in India; 
- Any income received or receivable from entertainment performed in India.

To compute total income, the following conditions must be satisfied under Section 8 of the Income-Tax Act, 2025:
(a) The employee has received gratuity; 
